  "id": "ALAS2023-2026-1680",
  "title": "Amazon Linux 2023 - ALAS2023-2026-1680: Medium priority package update for krb5",
  "issued": {
    "date": "2026-05-11 09:00:00"
  },
  "updated": {
    "date": "2026-05-11 09:00:00"
  },
  "severity": "Medium",
  "description": "Package updates are available for Amazon Linux 2023 that fix the following vulnerabilities:\nCVE-2026-40356:\n\tIn MIT Kerberos 5 (aka krb5) before 1.22.3, there is an integer underflow and resultant out-of-bounds read if an application calls gss_accept_sec_context() on a system with a NegoEx mechanism registered in /etc/gss/mech. An unauthenticated remote attacker can trigger this, possibly causing the process to terminate in parse_message.\n\nCVE-2026-40355:\n\tIn MIT Kerberos 5 (aka krb5) before 1.22.3, there is a NULL pointer dereference if an application calls gss_accept_sec_context() on a system with a NegoEx mechanism registered in /etc/gss/mech. An unauthenticated remote attacker can trigger this, causing the process to terminate in parse_nego_message.\n",
